# LearnFlow: Course Models Documentation

This document explains the data structure and logic behind the [courses/models.py](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py) file.

## 1. Core Hierarchy
The models follow a strict parent-child hierarchy to organize educational content:

[Category](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#4-15) ➔ [Course](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#16-29) ➔ [Module](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#30-53) ➔ [Lesson](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#54-73) / [Quiz](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#74-91)

---

## 2. Model Definitions

### Category
Groups courses for easier browsing (e.g., "Web Development", "Data Science").
- **Fields**: `title`, `slug` (unique identifier).

### Course
The main container for a subject.
- **Relationships**: 
    - `category`: FK to Category.
    - `instructor`: FK to User.
- **Fields**: `title`, `slug`, `overview`, `image`.

### Module
A chapter or section within a course.
- **Relationships**: 
    - [course](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/views.py#5-8): FK to Course.
- **Property: [completion_percentage](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#47-53)**:
    - Calculates progress based on the number of lessons marked as `is_done`.
    - **Logic**: [(Done Lessons / Total Lessons) * 100](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#74-91).

### Lesson
Individual teaching units (Video/Text).
- **Core logic**: 
    - `is_done`: Boolean to track if a student finished the lesson.
- **Fields**: `video_url`, `video_file`, `content` (Markdown support).

### Quiz
Assessments placed at the end of modules.
- **Fields**:
    - `pass_score`: Percentage needed to pass (default 70%).
    - `number_of_try`: **Global counter** (Currently tracks total attempts across all users).

### Question & Choice
Individual quiz interactions.
- **Question**: Belongs to a Quiz.
- **Choice**: Belongs to a Question. Has an `is_correct` flag used for scoring.

---

## 3. Results & Tracking

### QuizResult
Persistent record of a student's attempt.
- **Logic**: Created during [submit_quiz](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/views.py#39-82) view execution.
- **Fields**:
    - `user`: Which student took the quiz.
    - `total_score`: Number of correct answers.
    - [percentage](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#47-53): Calculated score.
    - `is_passed`: Boolean based on `Quiz.pass_score`.

---

## 4. Logical Notes
- **Ordering**: Modules, Lessons, and Quizzes all use an `order` field to ensure they appear in the correct sequence in the UI.
- **Slug Fields**: Used for SEO-friendly URLs instead of showing numeric IDs.
